      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAX BOSTONIA (1) has a strong record this trip with six wins and five placings from 16 starts. Missed the frame latest (36.61) when fourth over 630m at Nowra in a NG. Looks the one to beat with even luck. ERIZA SPARKLES (4) goes very well this course and distance starting eight times for four wins and three minors. Below best last time at Temora (25.60) in a NG, finishing a 5 length fourth. Suited here and expected to run well. COLD COLD NIGHT (2) turned in a moderate run last time when fifth at The Gardens over 400m behind Reborn Scarlett (23.08) in a Grade 5. Scored at his previous run. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Has ability and is one of the better chances. CUMBRIA BENNY (7) was a surprise last-start placegetter with solid claims again.",
